<F P=100> North Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   Article Cited Condemning U.S., ROK Military Moves </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Article Cited Condemning U.S., ROK Military Moves </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK3103105694 Pyongyang KCNA in English 1050 GMT 31 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK3103105694 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> ["Grave Provocations Driving Situation to Brink of War" -- </F>
KCNA headline] 
  [Text] Pyongyang, March 31 (KCNA) -- If the U.S. 
imperialists and the South Korean puppet clique dared ignite a 
war against us, our people and People's Army would deal a 
thousand-fold retaliatory blow at them, declares NODONG SINMUN 
in a by-lined article today. 
  The situation of the Korean peninsula is now being brought 
to 
the brink of war by the new war provocation moves committed by 
the U.S. imperialists and the South Korean puppet clique to 
stifle our Republic, the article says, and goes on: 
  The U.S. imperialists have brought the nuclear-powered 
carrier Carl Vinson near the Korean peninsula and deployed a 
naval fleet of 30 warships including two carrier task forces on 
the waters within a reach of 24 hours from the Korean coast for 
the resumption of the "Team Spirit" joint military exercises. 
  Meanwhile, a Patriot missile battalion involving 40 odd 
missile launching pads and over 800 troops left Texas for South 
Korea on the order of U.S. President Bill Clinton. 
  Availing itself of this situation, the Kim Yong-sam puppet 
clique has become all the more undisguised in its criminal war 
moves against the North. 
  The Kim Yong-sam group ordered all the puppet forces on to 
"a 
special alert" to keep them "prepared to attack the North," 
crying for "a tough reaction" against the North and "full 
preparations to invade the North through a cooperative system" 
with the United States. The puppets went so far as to make 
public a war plan against the North dubbed "New Operation Plan 
No. 5027." 
  The U.S. imperialists and the Kim Yong-sam puppet clique 
have 
staged very provocative and dangerous war gambles which might 
develop to a real war any time on the ground and in the air and 
the sea almost every day. 
  The danger of war on the Korean peninsula is imminent and 
real. 
  The U.S. imperialists intend to keep hold on South Korea 
indefinitely as their colony and, with it as the bridgehead, 
dominate the North of Korea and the rest of Asia. Intolerable 
are the crimes of the U.S. imperialists, who are trying to turn 
the Korean peninsula into the theatre of a thermonuclear war for 
their aggressive goal and of the Kim Yong-sam group, which is 
acting the shock brigade in executing their policy of aggression 
and war, courting their favor. 
  Our people and People's Army do not want a war. But they are 
not afraid of it. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS4-4302 </DOCNO>
