in Korean 1300 GMT 28 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> SK3103002294 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang Korean Central Broadcasting Network 
in Korean 1300 GMT 28 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=105> Korean </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The puppet prime minister showed up at the "Seoul 
City Police Office" on March 27 and ordered it to "maintain a 
perfect public peace and alert posture", according to a radio 
report from Seoul. 
  On March 26, while making a round of frontline units of the 
puppet Army, he incited war fever for a northward invasion, 
crying for a flawless "posture for countermove". 
  Facts that have been revealed show that the South Korean 
puppets are getting more frenzied with the passage of time in 
driving North-South relations to a phase of confrontation and 
war [taekyolgwa chonjaeng kungmyon]. 

</TEXT>

