<F P=100> North Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   ROK Dissident Reported Seeking Repeal of NSL </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    ROK Dissident Reported Seeking Repeal of NSL </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK3103103094 Pyongyang KCNA in English 1003 GMT 31 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK3103103094 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, March 31 (KCNA) -- The Rev. Kim Song-pok, 
chairman of the Independent Reunification Committee of the 
Inchon Federation for Democracy and Reunification of the 
Fatherland in South Korea, called for the repeal of the 
"National Security Law" (NSL) and the legalization of the 
National Alliance for the Country's Reunification (Pomminnyon). 
  In an article contributed to HANGYORE SINMUN on March 16, he 
urged the puppet authorities to scrap the NSL, an 
anti-reunification evil law, and send back to the North old men 
Kim In-so and Ham Se-hwan, who have been kept in prison in South 
Korea for refusing to be converted after they were arrested 
during the Korean war (June 25, 1950- July 27, 1953). 
  He also demanded that the authorities legalize the 
Pomminnyon, not branding it as an "organization benefitting the 
enemy", and guarantee the activation of the civilian 
reunification movement. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

