<F P=100> North Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   Church Groups Urge ROK To Oust Kim Yong-sam </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Church Groups Urge ROK To Oust Kim Yong-sam </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK3003233494 Pyongyang KCNA in English 1505 GMT 30 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK3003233494 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, March 30 (KCNA) -- The Korean 
Religionists Association (KRA) held an enlarged meeting here 
today calling on the South Korean religious organizations, 
clergymen and believers to take a resolute action for 
overthrowing the Kim Yong-sam regime of flunkeyist traitors for 
the reunification of the country in the 90s. 
  The meeting discussed measures concerning the refusal of the 
Kim Yong-sam puppet clique to allow the joint celebration of the 
centenary of the Kabo (1894) Peasants War by Chondoists in the 
North and the South. It was attended by members of the KRA and 
officials of the Central Guidance Committee of the Korean 
Chondoists Association, the Central Committee of the Korean 
Buddhists Federation, the Central Committee of the Korean 
Christians Federation and the Central Committee of the Korean 
Roman Catholics Association. 
  A relevant resolution and a letter to the South Korean 
religious organizations, clergymen and believers were adopted at 
the meeting. 
  The letter said the Kim Yong-sam regime's anti-national acts 
in blocking all the contacts and travel between the North and 
the South and the joint commemoration by the North and the South 
of the centenary of the peasants war, an anti-feudal, 
anti-aggression mass struggle of the nation, could never be 
justified and tolerated. 
  It noted that if such an anti-national group as the Kim 
Yong-sam clique, which takes no account of the nation and 
ancestors, were left in the country, neither the peace of the 
Korean peninsula nor the independent and peaceful reunification 
of the country could be expected and there would be only a 
nuclear holocaust. 
  It called on the South Korean religious organizations, 
clergymen and believers who love the country and the nation and 
hope for national reunification to decisively break with the Kim 
Yong-sam regime and join in the struggle for the establishment 
of a genuine independent, democratic government. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

