<F P=100> North Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   Japanese Bid for Permanent UNSC Seat Condemned </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Japanese Bid for Permanent UNSC Seat Condemned </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK3103054294 Pyongyang KCNA in English 0529 GMT 31 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK3103054294 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> ["Japan Not Qualified To Be UNSC Permanent Member'--KCNA </F>
headline] 
  [Text] Pyongyang, March 31 (KCNA) -- The Democratic 
Socialist Party, one of the seven ruling parties of Japan, 
Monday in its political platform for 1994 declared it would push 
for permanent membership in the UN Security Council (UNSC) as 
well as give its wholehearted support to UN operations, 
including peacekeeping activities, the KYODO News Service 
reported. 
  The Japanese authorities have revealed their intention to 
become a permanent member of the UN Security Council more than 
once. 
  It is an unbiased view of the international community that 
Japan has no justification and elementary qualification to seat 
itself at a responsible post of the United Nations. 
  It is ridiculous of Japan, a criminal state which provoked 
World War II, to seek UNSC permanent membership while having yet 
to atone for the unpardonable crimes and cleanse its dishonor as 
"enemy state" specified in the UN Charter. 
  Moreover, it is a reckless act for Japan to seek permanent 
membership while being criticised by unbiased public opinion for 
its grave threat to peace and security in Asia and its 
obstructions to the denuclearization of the Korean peninsula 
through the promotion of its nuclear armament on the pretext of 
the "nuclear issue" of the DPRK. 
  In trying to gain a permanent seat in the UNSC, Japan 
pursues 
the purpose of increasing its political say in the international 
arena, act a "leading state" and establish a "world order" 
militarily favorable for it. 
  The Japanese reactionaries must discard the foolish 
daydream, 
liquidate its past first of all and immediately renounce their 
scheme to convert Japan into a military power and arm it with 
nuclear weapons. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

