<F P=100> North Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   Architects Union Marks 40th Anniversary </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Architects Union Marks 40th Anniversary </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK3003053994 Pyongyang KCNA in English 0501 GMT 30 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK3003053994 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, March 30 (KCNA) -- The Korean Architects 
Union observed its 40th birthday. 
  The great leader President Kim Il-song founded the union in 
March 1954 in the difficult postwar period when everything had 
been razed to the ground. He has clearly indicated the path of 
the union in each stage of the revolutionary development. 
  The Central Committee of the Workers' Party of Korea sent a 
congratulatory message to the members of the union on its 40th 
birthday. 
  The message notes that over the past 40 years the union has 
actively helped to build Pyongyang and other cities and rural 
communities of Korea splendidly and modern industrial 
establishments and grand monumental edifices in different parts 
of the nation for the prosperity of the country and the 
improvement of the people's living standard. 
  The message highly estimates the union members for the great 
feats they have performed over the past 40 years in ushering in 
a brilliant heyday of chuche architecture in Korea. 
  A meeting was held here Tuesday to mark the anniversary. 

</TEXT>

