<F P=106> [UPI, YONHAP from Macao] </F>
  [Text] Relevant officials said on 30 March that North 
Korea had closed its trade office, which has so far issued visas 
in Macao. This office was one of the North Korean overseas 
offices dealing with the visa business throughout the world. 
  Since the mid-1970's, North Korea has operated its trade 
office in Macao. The office has received applications for visas 
since 1991. However, it has not disclosed the reason why it 
closed the office. 

</TEXT>

