<H3> <TI>   North `Propaganda Specialist' Defects to South </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    North `Propaganda Specialist' Defects to South </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK3103122094 Seoul YONHAP in English 1117 GMT 31 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK3103122094 </F>
<F P=104>  Seoul YONHAP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Seoul, March 31 (YONHAP) -- A North Korean man who 
worked as a propaganda specialist defected to South Korea on 
Thursday by way of a third country, the Agency for National 
Security Planning (NSP) reported. 
  The defector was identified as Kim Kwang-uk, age 26, a 
member 
of a mobile propaganda team of three revolutionary squads 
department, South Pyongan Province chapter of the Workers' 
(Communist) Party. 
  "Kim arrived at Kimpo Airport through a third country and 
asked for asylum in South Korea," an NSP official said. He said 
that a preliminary questioning showed that Kim graduated from 
Pyongsong Engineering College and escaped to China toward the 
end of last year while working as a mobile propaganda team 
member. 

</TEXT>

