<F P=100> Cambodia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Khmer Rouge Captures Two T-54 Tanks 29 Mar </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Khmer Rouge Captures Two T-54 Tanks 29 Mar </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK3103063694 (Clandestine) Voice of the Great National Union 
Front of Cambodia in Cambodian 2330 GMT 30 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK3103063694 </F>
<F P=104>  (Clandestine) Voice of the Great National Union 
Front of Cambodia </F>

<F P=105>  Cambodian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] On 28 March, the National Army of Democratic 
Kampuchea [NADK], in cooperation with the people, launched a 
commando attack on the Sala Krau position, killing seven enemy 
soldiers and seizing seven AK assault rifles. The remaining 
enemy troops were forced to retreat into the jungle. 
  On 29 March, the NADK attacked the 12th Division, which was 
temporarily stationed at Sala Krau. The fighting lasted five 
and a half hours. While the NADK was attacking the unit, four 
T-54 tanks and 200 ground troops were sent to help their 
companions. However, we killed 24 of them and wounded several 
others. We also burned two T-54 tanks, captured two others, and 
destroyed two military trucks. We also recaptured and reoccupied 
the summit of Srang Hill. We will continue to attack and 
destroy the remaining enemy troops at Sala Krau. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS4-4347 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "dreas062_i_94007" </HT>


<HEADER>
<AU>   FBIS-EAS-94-062 </AU>
Daily Report 
<DATE1>  30 Mar 1994 </DATE1>

</HEADER>

<F P=100> Cambodia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Townships of Moung, Bakan Attacked 28-29 Mar </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Townships of Moung, Bakan Attacked 28-29 Mar </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK3103072394 (Clandestine) Voice of the Great National Union 
Front of Cambodia in Cambodian 2330 GMT 30 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK3103072394 </F>
<F P=104>  (Clandestine) Voice of the Great National Union 
Front of Cambodia </F>

<F P=105>  Cambodian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] On 28 and 29 March, the people joined forces with 
the National Army of Democratic Kampuchea [NADK] in assaults 
against the invading forces of the communist Vietnamese puppets 
and two-headed government that had gathered at the Moung 
District township and the railway station to be shipped to the 
Pailin battlefield. 
  The communist Vietnamese puppets' state authorities had 
gathered their invading forces from diverse areas in Moung 
District at the district's township and railway station, from 
where they were to be sent as reinforcements to the Pailin 
region. When the people learned about this, they joined hands 
with the NADK to attack and disperse the soldiers. As a result, 
we killed 15 enemy soldiers and wounded more than 40 others. 
Taking that opportunity, many soldiers freshly recruited by the 
communist Vietnamese puppets' state authorities fled for home. 
The people and NADK also destroyed five barracks, eight 
vehicles, and 300 meters of railroad. 
  On the same day, the people and NADK attacked and destroyed 
the communist Vietnamese puppet' invading forces. They 
regrouped at Bakan District's township of Trapeang Chong on 
Route National 5, killing 17 enemy soldiers and wounding more 
than 20 others. 
  The state authorities of the communist Vietnamese puppets 
and 
two-headed government in Moung District and at Trapeang Chong 
were terrified and fled for their lives. Some run away to the 
Pursat provincial town, while others hid themselves at Boeng 
Khna in Svay Don Kev. 
  National Route 5 and the railway lines have been cut off 
since 28 and 29 March. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

