BFN 

  [Text] On the morning of 29 March, the high-level 
delegation of the House of Representatives of Malaysia [HRM] 
headed by His Excellency Tan Sri Datuk Mohamed Zahir bin Haji 
Ismail, speaker of the HRM, visited Xieng Khouang Province by a 
special plane. On hand at the Xieng Khouang airfield to warmly 
welcome the delegation was Phoumi Thipphavon, governor of Xieng 
Khouang Province; members of the provincial administrative 
committee; and a large number of cadres and Xieng Khouang 
residents. 
