delegation visited the Plain of Jars, Phonsavan town, and [words 
indistinct]. 
  On the morning of 30 March, the high-level HRM delegation 
led 
by its speaker and accompanied by Chaleun Yiapaoheu, member of 
the Standing Committee of the National Assembly, visited the 
Lao-Thai bridge construction site. The bridge is a gift from 
the Australian Government to the governments and peoples of Laos 
and Thailand. Its construction has been smooth and will be 
completed on schedule. The official opening of the bridge will 
be held in the near future. Later, the delegation visited a 
(?handicraft center) and a textile factory operated by the 
Federation of Lao Women's Unions. 

