<F P=102> BK3103014194 Hanoi VNA in English 1544 GMT 30 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> BK3103014194 </F>
<F P=104>  Hanoi VNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Hanoi VNA March 30 -- Prime Minister Vo Van Kiet 
received here today a high-level military delegation of Cambodia 
led by General Tie Banh and General Tea Chamrat, co-minister of 
national defence, now on a visit to Vietnam. 
  During the reception, Prime Minister Vo Van Kiet highly 
appreciated the relations of friendship between the two 
countries and the two national defence ministries. He noted 
that the Vietnamese people are very glad at the current 
development in Cambodia, and expressed his deep sympathy at 
difficulties and trials being undergone by the Cambodian people. 
The Vietnamese prime minister reaffirmed that the Vietnamese 
people would do all they could to, together with other countries 
in the region, support the Cambodian people in national 
construction and concord. [sentence as received] 
  On behalf of the Cambodian military delegation, General Tea 
Chamrat expressed his hope that the close neighbourliness 
between the peoples and militaries of Vietnam and Cambodia would 
be further developed in conformity with the aspiration of the 
two peoples and for peace, stability and prosperity. 
  General Tie Banh informed Prime Minister Vo Van Kiet of the 
situation of the Cambodian military, and expressed his belief 
that the people and military of Cambodia will be determined to 
overcome the difficulties and trials to build a peaceful and 
prosperous life. 
  In the same day, the Cambodian guests paid a tribute to Ho 
Chi Minh's mausoleum and called on his resident. [sentence as 
recieved] 

</TEXT>

