<F P=100> Thailand </F>
<H3> <TI>   Army Spokesman Denies Supporting Khmer Rouge </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Army Spokesman Denies Supporting Khmer Rouge </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK3103021794 Bangkok Radio Thailand Network in English 0000 
GMT 31 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK3103021794 </F>
<F P=104>  Bangkok Radio Thailand Network </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The Royal Thai Army has firmly denied the 
accusation that it has supported the Khmer Rouge guerrillas in 
their fight against Cambodian forces along the Thai-Cambodian 
border. 
  The Spokesman of the Royal Thai Army Colonel Phalangkun 
Klahan has made it clear that the Thai Government and the Royal 
Thai Army have always respected the UN resolution on the 
political solution to the war in Cambodia. The spokesman said 
the Royal Thai Army has not banned site inspections by foreign 
diplomats at any time. He added the Royal Thai Army has 
provided humanitarian aid to displaced Cambodians who fled from 
the fighting into Thailand and that the army did not forcibly 
repatriate those Cambodians. It is the Cambodian Government's 
responsibility to take care of its people affected by civil war 
or those who are displaced in their own country. 

</TEXT>

