<F P=100> Thailand </F>
<H3> <TI>   Army Commander Views Bombing of Train in South </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Army Commander Views Bombing of Train in South </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK3003143194 Bangkok Radio Thailand Network in Thai 1200 GMT 
30 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK3003143194 </F>
<F P=104>  Bangkok Radio Thailand Network </F>
<F P=105>  Thai </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Commenting on the sabotage of a train in the south, 
Army Commander in Chief General Wimon Wongwanit said that rifts 
among the ethnic people in the south are being exploited as a 
pretext to stage acts of terrorism. He said officials are doing 
their best in terms of suppression: 
  [Begin recording] [Wimon] I would like to say this -- 
suppression alone cannot solve the problem of terrorism, 
regardless of the country. We must try to cut their external 
support, and we will only be able to cut external support by 
negotiating with those countries on a government-to-government 
basis. Meanwhile, local people and soldiers must cooperate in 
safeguarding public security and protecting natural resources 
along the border. 
  [Unidentified correspondent] Was it an attempt to create 
confusion? 
  [Wimon] There is no confirmation of that. I have only 
received a report on the incident. It is still too early to 
determine what group was responsible for this attempt. We have 
to wait for more information and more evidence. [end recording] 

</TEXT>

