<F P=100> Vietnam </F>
<H3> <TI>   Cambodian Co-Defense Ministers on Official Visit </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Cambodian Co-Defense Ministers on Official Visit </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Meet With Defense Minister </H4>

<F P=102> BK3003162394 Hanoi Voice of Vietnam Network in Vietnamese 
2300 GMT 29 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK3003162394 </F>
<F P=104>  Hanoi Voice of Vietnam Network </F>
<F P=105>  Vietnamese </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] A high-level military delegation of the Kingdom of 
Cambodia led by Senior Generals Tie Banh and Tea Chamrat, 
co-ministers of defense, arrived in Hanoi yesterday on an 
official visit to our country at the invitation of Senior 
General Doan Khue, minister of national defense. 
  A solemn reception was held at the Ministry of National 
Defense guesthouse. Senior General Doan Khue, Vietnam's 
minister of national defense, heartily welcomed the two 
co-ministers of defense and the high-level military delegation 
of the Kingdom of Cambodia. He said he believed the visit will 
help consolidate the friendly relations between the two 
countries and two armies. 
  Senior General Tie Banh, speaking on behalf of Senior 
General 
Tea Chamrat and members of the delegation, expressed his thanks 
for the solemn reception by the Vietnamese National Defense 
Ministry. He also said he was confident the visit will have 
successful results. 
  In the afternoon, the high-level military delegation of the 
Kingdom of Cambodia held a meeting with a high-level Vietnamese 
military delegation. 

</TEXT>

