<F P=100> South Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   Japan Reportedly Detects No DPRK War `Signs' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Japan Reportedly Detects No DPRK War `Signs' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK0104041294 Seoul YONHAP in English 0253 GMT 1 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK0104041294 </F>
<F P=104>  Seoul YONHAP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Tokyo, April 1 (YONHAP) -- Japan has not detected 
any signs that North Korea is about to provoke a war against the 
South, despite rumors of a crisis on the peninsula caused by 
Pyongyang's suspected nuclear arms program, a Japanese newspaper 
quoted a Defense Ministry source as saying Friday. 
  The source, who has collected and analyzed various data on 
North Korean military moves, said the communist state is not in 
a state of extreme tension nor is it taking any preparatory 
action for war, the MAINICHI SHIMBUN reported. 
  "There is no strange sign in North Korea. We cannot catch 
any change in communications or frequency in North Korean 
military bases. They did not stop periodical reconnaissance 
flights either," the source was quoted as saying. 
  Defense Ministry staff do not think an emergency will arise 
at this stage, he said. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

