<H3> <TI>   High Privy Council Holds Meeting 29 Mar </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    High Privy Council Holds Meeting 29 Mar </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK0104022094 Phnom Penh National Radio of Cambodia Network 
in Cambodian 0500 GMT 30 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK0104022094 </F>
<F P=104>  Phnom Penh National Radio of Cambodia Network 
in Cambodian 0500 GMT 30 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=105> Cambodian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The High Privy Council held a working meeting at 
the Royal Palace on the morning of 29 March in the lofty 
presence of Privy Councillors Samdech Nhoek Chulong, Samdech 
Heng Samrin, Samdech Son Sann, Samdech Chau Senkosal, His 
Excellency [H.E.] Say Phuthang, H.E. Chea Soth, and H.E. Mat Ly. 
H.E. Kong Sam-ol, deputy prime minister of the Royal Palace, 
was also present. 
  The meeting focussed on the presence of the king of 
Cambodia, 
who will return and stay in the Royal Palace in early April. 
  The king will receive the people in audiences to solve their 
key problems, specifically problems dealing with the farmers' 
livelihood. The king is the last resort to solving, via the 
audiences, any problem that the government and National Assembly 
are not able to smooth out. 

</TEXT>

