<F P=100> South Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   Reaction to UNSC Statement on DPRK Reported </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Reaction to UNSC Statement on DPRK Reported </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Government: Statement `Appropriate' </H4>

<F P=102> SK0104022394 Seoul KBS-1 Radio Network in Korean 0130 GMT 1 
Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> SK0104022394 </F>
<F P=104>  Seoul KBS-1 Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Korean </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] In a statement issued by Foreign Ministry Spokesman 
Chang Ki-ho on 1 April, the government appraised it was an 
appropriate measure that the UN Security Council [UNSC] urged 
North Korea to accept additional inspections and requested the 
Secretary General of the International Atomic Energy Agency 
report the result of the negotiation. 
  The government said the UNSC presidential statement reflects 
the international community's deep concern over the seriousness 
of the North Korean nuclear issue and the resolute will to 
resolve the issue. He urged North Korea to immediately respond 
to the presidential statement. 

</TEXT>

