<H3> <TI>   Kankeiren To Appoint Kawakami Next Chairman </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Kankeiren To Appoint Kawakami Next Chairman </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW0104130494 Tokyo KYODO in English 1223 GMT 1 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW0104130494 </F>
<F P=104>  Tokyo KYODO </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Osaka, April 1 KYODO -- The Kansai Economic 
Federation will appoint Tetsuro Kawakami, chairman of Sumitomo 
Electric Industries Ltd., as its next chairman, federation 
officials said Friday [1 April]. The Federation, known as 
Kankeiren, will officially approve the appointment at a regular 
general board meeting to be held May 22. 
  Kankeiren will also newly appoint nine vice chairmen. Among 
them, Hiroshi Ohba, president of Kawasaki Heavy Industries Ltd., 
and Kenji Kawakatsu, chairman of Sanwa Bank, will continue in 
their current vice presidential positions. 
  Kyocera Corp. Chairman Kazuo Inamori and Sekisui House Ltd. 
President Isao Okui will be newly appointed as vice chairmen of 
the business leaders' organization based in Osaka. The average 
age of the chairman and vice chairmen will be 64, younger than 
73-year average of the current executive lineup, they said. 

</TEXT>

