<H3> <TI>   Border Inspection Delegation Returns From PRC </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Border Inspection Delegation Returns From PRC </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK0304154494 Rangoon Radio Burma in Burmese 1330 GMT 3 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> BK0304154494 </F>
<F P=104>  Rangoon Radio Burma </F>
<F P=105>  Burmese </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] A seven-member Myanmar [Burmese] delegation led by 
Naval Captain Tun Aung, director general of the Land Survey 
Department of the Ministry of Forestry, returned to Yangon 
[Rangoon] by Myanmar Airways International last night after 
attending the third meeting of the Joint Inspection Committee 
for the second Myanmar-Chinese joint boundary inspection in 
Beijing, People's Republic of China, from 23 March to 1 April. 
  The Myanmar and Chinese delegation led by Mr. Su Wiyi, the 
ambassador of PRC's Ministry of Foreign Affairs, held 
discussions and agreed on the repair of dilapidated border 
markers in accordance with the provisions of the Myanmar-Chinese 
Boundary protocol. The delegations also agreed on the matters 
concerning the second joint boundary inspection to install new 
border markers and the drafting of a protocol on the second 
Myanmar-Chinese boundary inspection. The leaders of the 
delegations also signed the minutes of the meeting on these 
agreements on 1 April. 

</TEXT>

