<H3> <TI>   53,409 Refugees Repatriated From Bangladesh </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    53,409 Refugees Repatriated From Bangladesh </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK0204090094 Rangoon Radio Burma in Burmese 0630 GMT 2 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> BK0204090094 </F>
<F P=104>  Rangoon Radio Burma </F>
<F P=105>  Burmese </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] In accordance with the coordinated agreement 
reached between the two countries on the repatriation of those 
who had illegally left Myanmar [Burma] for Bangladesh, a 
delegation led by Camp Supervisor Mr. Rashidul Islam from the 
country on the other side [Bangladesh], transferred 61 returnees 
from 12 households to our Kanyinchaung reception center on the 
morning of 30 March. The returnees were brought in by two 
schooners. 
  Since the repatriation of those who left the country 
illegally began on 22 February 1992 [date as heard], a total of 
53,409 persons from 11,990 households have been accepted through 
30 March 1994. 

</TEXT>

