<H3> <TI>   Muslim Insurgent Surrenders in Tenasserim </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Muslim Insurgent Surrenders in Tenasserim </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK0204145994 Rangoon Radio Burma in Burmese 1330 GMT 2 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> BK0204145994 </F>
<F P=104>  Rangoon Radio Burma </F>
<F P=105>  Burmese </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Members of jungle-based armed organizations have 
been returning to the legal fold along with their arms and 
ammunitions at various garrisons. This is because they have 
realized their wrongdoings and have gained correct views. They 
have also accepted and have faith in the genuine goodwill and 
activities of the State Law and Order Restoration Council. 
  Mulaki alias Pwint Lin, 35, the son of U Ba Sin of Katokan 
Village, Tenasserim Township and the platoon leader of the 
Muslim armed organization in the jungle, returned to the legal 
fold at Tenasserim garrison on 13 March 1994. He brought in one 
AK-47 assault rifle, one magazine, and 20 rounds of ammunition. 

</TEXT>

