<F P=100> Brunei, Malaysia &amp; Singapore </F>
<F P=101> Malaysia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Mahathir Urges Sabahans To Discard Parochialism </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Mahathir Urges Sabahans To Discard Parochialism </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK0304090394 Kuala Lumpur Voice of Malaysia in English 0600 
GMT 3 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK0304090394 </F>
<F P=104>  Kuala Lumpur Voice of Malaysia </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Prime Minister Datuk Sri Dr. Mahathir Mohamed has 
urged the people of Sabah to discard parochialism. They should 
regard themselves as Malaysian in equal terms with people in the 
other states. Speaking at a gathering in Kota Kinabalu, the 
prime minister said the spirit of solidarity is important for 
the people to discard any feelings of alienation. Everyone in 
the country enjoys the same rights, including holding top posts 
regardless of the state of origin, community, or religion. 
Datuk Sri Dr. Mahathir added that federal government 
supervision of the new Sabah administration is necessary to 
ensure that the abuses of past governments do not recur. The 
supervision is not deemed as colonizing Sabah but to make sure 
that the state is administered well. 

</TEXT>

