<H3> <TI>   Reaction to U.S. Report on Trade Barriers </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Reaction to U.S. Report on Trade Barriers </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Hosokawa Responds </H4>

<F P=102> OW0204024894 Tokyo Nikkei Telecom Database in Japanese 2 Apr 
94--FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> OW0204024894 </F>
<F P=104>  Tokyo Nikkei Telecom Database </F>
<F P=105>  Japanese </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [From NIHON KEIZAI SHIMBUN 1 April Evening Edition] </F>
  [Text] The U.S. trade representative has released an 
annual report on foreign trade barriers that cites the 
procurement of the Japanese Government. Asked by a group of 
reporters in the Diet building to comment on the annunal report, 
Prime Minister Hosokawa said: "The annual report urges the 
Japanese Government to map out another package of measures to 
open up the Japanese market by June. From now on, the government 
will take voluntary measures to open up the Japanese market." 
In this way, the prime minister stressed that the Japanese 
Government plans to do everything in its power to map out 
another package of measures during June to open markets in Japan. 

</TEXT>

