<H3> <TI>   MOPT Ready To Talk to U.S. on Procurement </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    MOPT Ready To Talk to U.S. on Procurement </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW0204015994 Tokyo Nikkei Telecom Database in Japanese 2 Apr 
94--FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> OW0204015994 </F>
<F P=104>  Tokyo Nikkei Telecom Database </F>
<F P=105>  Japanese </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [From MAINICHI SHIMBUN 2 April Morning Edition] </F>
  [Text] The U.S. trade representative has released an 
annual report on foreign trade barriers that calls on Japan to 
improve the current procedures of procurement by the Nippon 
Telegraph and Telephone Corporation (NTT). In response, the 
Ministry of Posts and Telecommunications [MOPT] made clear on 1 
April that it is ready to negotiate with the United States in 
April, at the earliest. The NTT announced a set of measures to 
revamp its current procurement procedures, including free 
contracts, in response to a package of external economic 
measures that the government announced on 29 March. The MOPT 
expressed a willingness to negotiate with the United States with 
the aim of briefing that country on the measures announced by 
the NTT. 
  Japan and the United States have concluded an 
intergovernmental agreement on NTT's procurement. An annual 
review of the NTT's procurement is to be conducted in accordance 
with the agreement, but the 1993 review has yet to be undertaken. 

</TEXT>

