<F P=101> Japan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Hata Sees Dynamism in Competition With LDP </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Hata Sees Dynamism in Competition With LDP </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW0304062194 Tokyo Nikkei Telecom Database in Japanese 3 Apr 
94--FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> OW0304062194 </F>
<F P=104>  Tokyo Nikkei Telecom Database </F>
<F P=105>  Japanese </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [From NIHON KEIZAI SHIMBUN 3 April Morning Edition] </F>
  [Text] On 2 April, Tsutomu Hata, deputy prime minister and 
concurrently foreign minister, gave a lecture at a meeting held 
by a group mainly composed of junior bureaucrats for the purpose 
of exchanging views among different professions. In dealing 
with the realignment of political parties, Hata said: "It is out 
of the question (that the coalition parties) should act as if 
they were five horses heading in different directions while 
pulling the same carriage. Efforts must be made to unite the 
coalition parties in one way or another because political 
dynamism now lies in competition with the Liberal Democratic 
Party [LDP]." In this way, Hata reiterated his intention to 
promote the plan for forming a new party and coordinate the 
selection of coalition-supported candidates for the next House 
of Representatives' election. 

</TEXT>

